itemDescription: leader of the Scottish National Party from 1956 until 1960

wikipedia_page.main: James Halliday (27 February 1927 – 3 January 2013) was a Scottish author, historian and politician. He was the chairman (leader) of the Scottish National Party (SNP) from 1956 to 1960.

response: *Jimmy Halliday (1927–2013), leader of the Scottish National Party (1956–1960)
